This paper discusses the architecture and techniques for efficient wireless powering of IoT devices, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). It also discusses the use of channel state information (CSI) for wireless powering, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the need for resource allocation strategies, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and energy technology and management (cs.ETM).
